service_description: This is a [link:serverLink]crowdsourced distributed cluster[/link] of [link:imageWorkerLink]image generation workers[/link] and [link:textWorkerLink]text generation workers[/link]. If you like this service, consider [link:joinHordeLink]joining the horde yourself[/link]!
more_information: For more information, visit the [link:faqLink]FAQ[/link]. Finally, you can also follow the [link:developerBlogLink]main developer's blog[/link].
stats.realtime: You can see the horde activity (including past stats) on [link:grafanaLink]Grafana[/link]
quickstart.register_account: First register an account which will generate for you an API key. Store that key somewhere.
quickstart.anonymous_api_key: if you do not want to register, you can use [b]'0000000000'[/b] as an api key to connect anonymously. However anonymous accounts have the lowest priority when there's too many concurrent requests!
quickstart.explanation_api_key: To increase your priority you will need a unique API key and then to increase your Kudos. [link:kudosExplanationLink]Read how Kudos are working[/link].
guis.description.horde_ng: HordeNG aims to be very simple to use for beginners, while allowing the full set of options for advanced users.
transfer.visit_old: If you would like to log in using one of the account providers (Google, Discord, Github), you might need to use [link:oldUrl]the old version of the transfer page[/link].
transfer.source_api_key.description: Type the API key that belongs to your user
invalid_api_key: The api key is not valid
transfer.kudos_amount.description: How many kudos do you want {{user}} to receive
transfer.success: The kudos have been successfully transferred!
transfer.error: There was an error while transferring the kudos, please try again later.
transfer.too_many_kudos: Eh, you don't have that many kudos
transfer.donate: or donate them to one of the educator accounts:
